The Herald Today was the ZANU-PF National Cell day. President Mnangagwa, the First Secretary of the ruling party, together with the First Family attended their party cell meeting at Dambudzo 1 cell in Sherwood, Kwekwe. Dambudzo cell has 59 members including the First Family. The party introduced this day as a way of strengthening its grassroots and mobilization units. This year’s National Cell Day marks the beginning of a membership recruitment and voter mobilisation exercise as the party targets 5 million votes. A cell consists of 50 members. As of February 2022, the Party had 78 000 cells which approximates to 3.9 million members. The ZANU PF Dambudzo Cell 1 Chairman is Cde Augustine Gijima. – Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services